VERDICT: APPROVED_WITH_COMMENTS
The diff successfully delivers the core task: Registration is now a 6-step wizard with a step indicator/progress bar, step-specific fields matching the requested sections, Back/Next navigation, animated step transitions, a canvas-based signature component on step 6, a submit flow, and a post-submit confirmation screen with chamber contact details. Home hero was redesigned with a full-height (min 700px) background image, dark overlay, white readable text, stronger CTA styling, and an added stats strip for visual depth.

Critical findings / analysis:
- Registration wizard architecture is solid and aligned to scope (client-side only, no backend persistence).
- Step content coverage is strong and corresponds to the requested six sections.
- Success state is appropriately branded and contains admin email/phone/location as requested.
- Hero redesign materially improves visual impact and readability while keeping existing page structure intact.
- Non-blocking functional gap: required-field enforcement is not step-gated. Because Next buttons are `type="button"` and each step is conditionally rendered, users can skip required fields in earlier steps and still submit. This does not break rendering but weakens form integrity.
- Non-blocking gap: step 6 signature is not enforced as required at submit time (empty signature can be submitted).

Security: none observed (no serious auth/injection/secret handling issues introduced; changes are client-side UI/state only).

